      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Just left with the three runners after some scratchings, including the main danger to the favourite. No spoils at the price but it does look all NEVER ORDINARY (2) in the opener. The Dirty Work filly impressed on debut when only missing by a lip to the promising Rebel Tuesday, who has since run well in the G3 Ottawa Stakes at Flemington. Improvement to come, so she shouldn't have too much trouble taking care of this small field. NEVEU (3) is a Rich Enuff gelding on debut for the O'Connor yard. Has jumped out well in readiness, though does look up against it here. TIKKAMOS (4) also debuts and is another that has been solid in his lead-up work but looks to have found a sharp one at his first start.",
